abstract={Since the establishment of Institution of Civil Engineers (ICE) in UK in 1818, the consulting industries have been developing for nearly 200 years. With the rapid development of the worldwide second-wave industrial revolution at the turns of 1900s, consulting industries become urgently needed owning to the social divisions of labor and sophistication of enterprises operations. As for the United States, the origination of management consulting bears deep relation with the scientific management thought of Taylor, and the direct origination is considered as the amalgam of three professions (engineering, law and accounting) and consulting roles of merchant bankers owning to the separation of commercial and investment banks in Depression period around 1930s. The rapid expansion of Chicago and New York-based management consultants and Boston-based consulting engineers lays the foundations of consulting industry for US as well as the world. Chicago acts as the center of US manufacturing and hinterland markets, the agglomeration the of large corporation headquarters would illustrate the fact that it also acts as the major center of management consulting firms during this period. The civil transferring of military strategic institutions and their demonstration provides more possibilities for the development of strategic consulting firms after the Second World War. With the free expertise under Marshall Plan since 1950s, European enterprises are willing to pay managerial guidance of consulting firms, which make it easy for US consulting firms to expand their international businesses. As a result, more consulting enterprises establish their worldwide strategic business unites. Large consulting firms like McKinsey & Co. move their headquarters from Chicago to New York, the easier place for international services at strategic finance and logistics. With the undergoing of Europe Americanization, dissemination of US business models prevails, leaving the opportunities of Boston-based academic-intensive consulting firms such as Boston Consulting Group. The Middle East oil crisis since mid-1970s bring about another radical change for US economy. Cost reduction and structure reorganization becomes radical for the second time, Chicago-rooted management consulting firms, which are good at management of audit, taxation and reorganization (like Anderson), find their values and dominated the consulting markets for a long time. With the outward transferring of traditional manufacturing unites and arising of IT supported knowledge economy since 1990s, US corporations become leading forces through network-based global value chain governance. The management and strategic consulting firms become the outpost forces of world Americanization. Three streams of US based consulting forces looms at large since this period. They are Chicago-rooted reorganization-intended consulting firms, New York-rooted integration-intended consulting firms and Boston-rooted innovation-intended consulting firms. US top consulting firms comes into China in early 1980s mainly at technical consulting with import of technologies and instruments; US and European multinationals comes to China in the form of joint-ventures, bring about the special consulting firms of law and accounting in mid-1980s; Management consulting firms like McKinsey & Co. comes to China in late 1980s, acting as the disseminators of American consulting thoughts. With the reform of Chinese state-run enterprises into stock companies in 1990s, international strategic consulting firms in finance begin to land China. The trajectory of US consulting firms location is from Hong Kong to Shanghai and Bejjing. Their sphere of varies from international investors to domestic enterprises, and from private enterprises to local governments. Advantages of US consulting firms mainly at their regulatory operation, rich experiences, trustworthy behaviors and excellent talents, but there are still several problems such as superficial understanding of Chinese consulting market, west-east cultural conflicts and competitions from domestic rivals. Facing the problems above, the US consulting firms takes strategic actions of localization through employing Chinese talents with overseas education, and joint-training with local educational / academic institutes. Local consulting firms grow up since late 1970s and early 1980s in China. Government invested management and strategic consulting institutes that serve planned sectors and projects begin to establish during this period. Private consulting firms and institutes emerge mainly at information survey and management consulting in early 1990s. At mid 1990s, there is radical change from pure idea and concoctive firms into professional consulting firms. Well-trained MBA and entrepreneurs enter consulting industries at late 1990s, accompanying the establishment of partnership consulting firms. Three major streams of in China: the first force should be overseas consulting firms (like McKinsey & Co.) with market-share of about 50%, the second force is several local consulting firms with annual revenue exceeding 10 million RMB, 10-20%, and the third force is thousands of SMEs with 1-10 million annual revenue. Chinese local consulting firms locate at three areas of Shanghai-centered investment-intensive Yangtze River region, Hong Kong /Shenzhen-centered market-intensive pan Pearl River region, and information-intensive region of Beijing, but there are still no obvious functional features like the consulting clusters from Chicago, New York and Boston. The advantages of local consultancies are familiarity with local conditions, flexibilities, and low prices, but there are still several disadvantages of small scales, minor reputations, lacking of data banks and excellent talents. Are there any necessities for mutual learning and any ways for strategic alliances? The authors of the paper try to probe into the future co-existence of US and domestic consulting firms via perspectives between McKinsey & Co. and ZG Wang Strategic Consultancy in regional rail consulting programs of Yangtze River Delta and Pearl River Delta. © 2005 IEEE.},
